Alignment_by_numbers
Created by Avraam Tapinos on 10/08/2015.
Copyright 2015 University of Mnachester (UoM). All rights reserved.
Version 0.1
Last revision 0.1.



"--Alignment by numbers--";
Usage:
Parameters:
    -fa [~/reference_genome.fasta]    -- (Required parameter) fasta file directory and file name

    -fq [~/reads_file.fastq]          -- (Required parameter) fastq file directory and file name
    
    -o [~/outputdirectory]            -- (Optional parameter) output directory to save the alignment sam file. If not provided the sam file is save in the same directory as the fastq file.

    -kmer [x]                         -- (Optional parameter) kmer size to use for the analysis [default: 100]

    -rep [Representation method]      -- (Optional parameter) Provide the representation method to use for converting nucleotide sequences to numerical sequences [default: Voss_indicators]
        Options:
            01) Atomic_Numbers
            02) Complex_Numbers
            03) Dna_Walk
            04) EIIP_numbers
            05) Integer_numbers
            06) Pair_numbers
            07) Real_numbers
            08) Tetrahedron
            09) Voss_indicators       --         default option
            10) Z_curve

    -tra [Transformation method]      -- (Optional parameter) Provide the transformation method to use for compressing data to a lower dimensional space [default: DFT]\n";
        Options:\
            01) DFT                   --         default option
            02) DWT
            03) PAA

    -clvl [y]                         -- (Optional parameter) compression level to use for the analysis [default: 2]

    -knn [kn]                         -- (Optional parameter)the number of kn neighbor data to use for the KNN search [default: 100]

    -m [m]                            -- (Optional parameter) the number of m partitions to make for each vantage point in the indexing structure [default: 2]

    -v [v]                            -- (Optional parameter) the number of v vantage points to use in each branch [default: 1]

    -k [v]                            -- (Optional parameter) the maximum number of k data values to be stored in an each leaf node in the indexing structure [default: knn]

    -rad [x.xxx]                      -- (Optional parameter) the radius value to use during the knn search [default: individual double value calculated based on the length of the kmer selected and the compression level applied on the data]

    -h                                -- Print Help Options

    Example:
    01) Alignment_by_numbers -fa ~/genome.fasta -fq ~/reads.fastq
    02) Alignment_by_numbers -fa ~/genome.fasta -fq ~/reads.fastq -kmer 300 -rep Tetrahedron -tra DWT -clvl 4 -knn 30
    03) Alignment_by_numbers -fa ~/genome.fasta -fq ~/reads.fastq -kmer 300 -rep Tetrahedron -tra DWT -clvl 4 -knn 30 -m 4 -v 2 -k 50 -rad 0.5
